FBIS4-27012 "drchi125_a_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Meets Indian, Canadian Guests Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Meets Indian, Canadian Guests OW2806140894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1358 GMT 28 Jun 94 OW2806140894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, June 28 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua met with Satish Sharma, Indian minister of state for petroleum and natural gas, and Andre Desmarais, president of the Power Corporation of Canada, on separate occasions here this afternoon. Zou told the Indian guest that Sino-Indian ties have grown smoothly in recent years, and China will actively engage in cooperation with other countries, especially its neighbors. He said the Chinese Government supports China's petroleum industry in its efforts to cooperate with foreign countries. Zou noted that China adheres to two principles in such relations, namely, equality and mutual benefit, and long-term cooperation. He hoped that Sino-Indian cooperation in the fields of oil and natural gas would develop without a hitch. Sharma and his party, guests of the China National Petroleum and Gas Corporation, arrived in Beijing on June 26. In his meeting with Desmarais and his party, Zou said China welcomes the Canadian Power Corporation to enter into cooperation with China in power, mining and other fields. Desmarais and his party came to China at the invitation of the China International Trust and Investment Corporation.
